The state capture commission chaired by deputy chief justice Raymond Zondo is expected to hear testimony related to Bosasa on Thursday. In a statement, the commission said suspended SA Civil Aviation Authority official Mbulelo Gingcana will give Bosasa-related evidence. “The commission will also hear Bosasa-related evidence from former  COO Angelo Agrizzi to be cross-examined by Mr [Kevin] Wakeford's legal representative and Mr Richard le Roux to be cross-examined by Mr Gingcana's legal representative,” the commission said.